.TH riff 1 


.SH NAME
	riff - Raw Image File Flasher

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B	riff [OPTION]...[FILE]...


.SH DESCRIPTION
.br
riff flashes a device with a raw image file.


.SH OPTIONS
.B	-h, --help 
.br
Prints a breif description of the command-line options.

.B	-m ACTION, --mode ACTION
.br
Use ACTION to select flash, erase or dump mode.

.B	-c PATH, --config PATH
.br
Give path to the configuration file.

.B	-f IMAGEPATH, --flashimage IMAGEPATH
.br
Give path the flashimage.

.B	-a FLASHADDR, --address FLASHADDR
.br
Give a start address in hex.

.B -l HEXLENGTH, --length HEXLENGTH
.br
Length of the dump [Byte] in hex.

.B -d DUMPPATH, --dumppath DUMPPATH
.br
File path on PC where to store dump.

.B	-v, --verbose
.br
Shows more detailed information.

.B      --version
.br
Shows version information.

